---
name: fix-task
version: 1.0.0
description: Parent post-triage fix assignment template for cursor-orchestration QA findings (rust-developer Task).
format: xml
required_variables:
  - task_id
  - phase
  - sprint_doc
  - branch
  - worktree_path
  - pr_target
  - description
  - finding_ids
  - triage_records
  - required_fixes
  - acceptance_criteria
  - references
optional_variables:
  - validation_requirements
defaults:
  validation_requirements: ""
---
<cursor-task id="{{ task_id }}" phase="{{ phase }}" assignee="rust-developer" mode="fix">
  <description>{{ description }}</description>

  <branch>{{ branch }}</branch>
  <worktree>{{ worktree_path }}</worktree>
  <pr-target>{{ pr_target }}</pr-target>
  <authoritative-sprint-doc>{{ sprint_doc }}</authoritative-sprint-doc>

  <finding-ids>
{{ finding_ids }}
  </finding-ids>

  <triage-records>
{{ triage_records }}
  </triage-records>

  <required-fixes>
{{ required_fixes }}
  </required-fixes>

  <acceptance-criteria>
{{ acceptance_criteria }}
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <validation-requirements>
{{ validation_requirements }}
  </validation-requirements>

  <references>
{{ references }}
  </references>

  <workflow>
    <step id="a">ACK this Task immediately. Begin work in the same session unless blocked.</step>
    <step id="b">Read `{{ sprint_doc }}` before editing. Treat it as the authoritative source for sprint scope, retained requirements, deletion targets, validation, and acceptance criteria. If this assignment summary and the sprint doc differ, the sprint doc wins and the mismatch must be reported.</step>
    <step id="c">Update the assigned worktree from the target branch before editing. Include all earlier-sprint fixes already merged forward to that branch.</step>
    <step id="d">Read the referenced triage records first. Treat the listed occurrences as the minimum required scope on this branch.</step>
    <step id="e">Fix every promoted-branch occurrence in scope. Do not stop at the first location when the triage record marks the finding as repeatable.</step>
    <step id="f">As soon as the branch is pushable, commit and push immediately. Report branch name and commit hash so the parent can re-run QA via cursor-quality-mgr.</step>
    <step id="g">Run the required validation after the push report and send a second report with PASS or FAIL plus concrete failure details.</step>
    <step id="h">Stop after the validation report. Wait for a new parent Task; do not poll ATM mail.</step>
  </workflow>
</cursor-task>
